* ============================================================
* SQLITE_SMOKE.DTS
* Basic smoke test for DotTalk++ SQLITE command.
* - Creates an in-memory DB, makes a table, inserts a few rows, SELECTs, then closes.
* Keep ASCII only.
* ============================================================

ECHO ===== SQLITE SMOKE START =====

SQLITE VERSION

* Open in-memory
SQLITE OPEN :memory:

* Create + insert
SQLITE EXEC CREATE TABLE t (id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY, name TEXT, n INTEGER);
SQLITE EXEC INSERT INTO t (name, n) VALUES ('alpha', 10);
SQLITE EXEC INSERT INTO t (name, n) VALUES ('bravo', 20);
SQLITE EXEC INSERT INTO t (name, n) VALUES ('charlie', 30);

* Query
SQLITE SELECT SELECT id, name, n FROM t ORDER BY id;

* Close
SQLITE CLOSE

ECHO ===== SQLITE SMOKE END =====
